Paper: hep-th/9410019

Date: 1994-10-04

Title: Horizon Condition Holds Pointwise on Finite Lattice with Free Boundary

ConditionsAuthors: M.Schaden and D.Zwanziger

Comments: 8 Latex pages, NYU-94-SZ2

It is proven that the "horizon condition", which was found to characterizethe fundamental modular region in continuum theory and the thermodynamic limitof gauge theory on a periodic lattice, holds for every (transverse)configuration on a finite lattice with free boundary conditions.